SUBJECTIVE: Patient reports she is feeling better today with her pain. Patient reports that without her medications she would be in a huge ammount of pain. Patient states that the physical therapy in combination with her medicine is more effective than medication alone.
Patient Goals: 0-10 Scale (0=no problem 10=unable to perform) -Going down steps 7 -Squatting 9 -Sitting 15 min. 6
Pain: 8/10
OBJECTIVE: -CT-Scan 3/13/15 show: minimal degenerative changes. Minimal spurring of the patella bilaterally, and joint space narrowing of the lateral compartment of the R knee joint.
Observation: -No change in patients symptoms or objective findings
Outcome Measures: Mobility: -Scoring: 1-4; 1=Totally Dependent 2=Requires assistance of a person (with or without appliance), 3=Requires appliances, orthosis or prosthesis for independence, 4=Totally independent (indoors/outdoors), -Ambulation: 4 -Transfers: 4 -Wheelchair: 4 -Total: 12/12
Education Provided: -Patient and daughter instructed to gradually increase the repetitions for straight leg raise flexion abduction and sit to stand from an elevated seat. Instruction was also provided as to attempting to perform step ups on a 4 height, if able to be done safely at home.
Patient/Caregiver demonstrated understanding of the education: Yes
Need for Physical Therapy services: Yes
Prognosis with Physical Therapy: Fair (due to fear avoidance behavior)
Need for other Rehabilitation Medicine Department services: Yes; PT
Need for rehabilitation services post discharge: Yes; Out-patient physical therapy for back, joint and leg pain.
PLAN: Discharge patient from physical therapy to independent with home exercise program. Patient to seek referral to local physical therapy services if his symptoms are not significantly improved over the next week.
Goals: (8/4/15) (met) -patient independent with home exercise program prior to discharge
Patient/Caregiver participated in and agreed to the development of the plan of care and treatment goals.
Patient/Caregiver to contact physical therapist with any questions or concerns regarding physical therapy assessment and treatment.
